[49m[38;5;9m- 403     [0m:[38;5;9m[49m **Per-cohort monitoring is non-negotiable.** Aggregate metrics hide failures that subgroup metrics surface. The bot's performance across language, age proxies, channel, and (where appropriate) other cohort axes is monitored from day one. Disparity alerts trigger reviews.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      403[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Per-cohort monitoring is non-negotiable.** Aggregate metrics hide failures that subgroup metrics surface. The bot's performance across language, channel, region, category, and content-type axes is monitored from day one. Single-axis cohorts (per-language, per-channel, per-region, per-category) are the minimum; two-axis combinations (per-language-by-channel, per-language-by-category) surface equity-acute disparities. Per-cohort minimum sample sizes prevent noise from masquerading as signal. Per-cohort threshold metrics (containment rate, retrieval quality, scope-violation rate, crisis-detection rate, handoff rate, patient-feedback distribution) are launch gates, not post-launch dashboards. Institution-wide averages are informational only; launch is gated on every cohort meeting its threshold. Disparity alerts trigger reviews. Sustained disparity triggers remediation tracking owned by patient-experience and clinical-quality leadership with quarterly review cadence.
